    'topic' => 'Why multiple FTL\'s?',
    'body' => 'So, does anyone think that the gas giant dwellers would
be interested in a drive that gave them 2C?

I don\'t have the ref handy, but they were presented
in an early JTAS and are "allergic" to jumpspace.

Now, no sane human would use this drive ("I\'m not going
to take 6 yrs to go Jump-1") for interstellar travel,
but there are a few larger systems where it could be
used for interplanetary transport.

There is actually a good range of possibilities that can
be covered in this way, but you have to watch out for
"incompatible" FTL methods.  Maybe under-powering a Jump
field generator only warps the space instead of penetrating
it, allowing for "slow" FTL, maybe there is a different
drive geometry involved, or a different type of energy
field.  Overpower your meson screens and perhaps you get
a boost to your manuever drives ;)  The possibilities
are nearly endless.  It is just a matter of finding a combo
that works.

Daniel Taylor   

