Right now here is a rough break down (guestmates actually) of the traffic of
the combined list (if someone wants to go through the digests and count them
feel free to):

    System Comparison:  30%   (i.e. I like CT better, no I like TNE)
    MMT Related         40%   (Skills, weapons etc.  Carries a lot of the above
                               with it)
    TNE Related:        3%
    MT Related:         3%
    CT Related:         3%
    Generic to all:     10%
    Admin:              10%
    Other:              1%

Right now, about 50% of the traffic (not all of the first two catagories) is
being cross posted.  If the lists are used like they should be, only the
Generic and Admin should be cross posted.

Personally, I like the idea of one list -- it makes my life easier.  But I
am not objectionable to more either.  However, we don\'t know what T4 will
look like.  When TNE came out it alienated a bunch of people.  When T4 comes
out it could: a) Tick off the CT/MT crowd again, b) Tick off the TNE crowd,
or c) make the world a happy place (which is the one I am cheering for).  At
the point that T4 comes out, we may want to create a TNE refuge, just like
we did for Xboat.  But it doesn\'t change the Traveller Charter, which is to
discuss Traveller regardless of version.

So in the mean time, until T4 comes out, I don\'t want to make any changes,
but the level of cross posting is out of control, so I am reminding people
of the charters of both lists.  My recommendation is instead of combining
the lists, limit MMT to one to reduce the large amounts of cross posts and
let the lists do their thing and serve their charters.

