    'topic' => 'The Imperium (lots of questions)',
    'body' => '>From: "Stuart L. Dollar" <sdollar@goodnet.com>

>On 21 Jun 96 at 15:13, Jamie Young spewed:

>> What did the Emperor\'s job involve?  I assume he/she must have had real
>> power otherwise the position would\'nt be worth killing for.  On a similar
>> vein, what was the source of the Emperor\'s wealth - was he obliged to live
>> off the revenues of his own estates or could he raid the Imperial treasury
>> at will?
>
>The Imperial family had vast holdings in most of the megacorporation, as
well as fiefs >on numerous worlds.  Don\'t know about your comments on
raiding the Imperial treasury, >but if their holdings in the megacorps
amounted to what they should, I doubt any of the >Emperors ever wanted for
money.  Somebody else could probably answer this question >better than I could.

I assume that during the Civil War, venality figured as much as power-lust
in many, if not most, of the attempts to seize the throne.  As rich as
admirals no doubt were, the wealth controlled by the Imperial family would
be orders of magnitude greater, and thus tempting.  The ability to raid the
treasury to finance repair, upgrading, and additions to the
Admiral/Emperor\'s fleet would also have some appeal.  In addition, while
probably all of the admirals involved were nobles, the power of the emperor
was orders of magnitude greater -- including the ability to make new nobles
- -- and also tempting.  

Other than during that period, however, I think Stu is right that the
emperors never wanted for money (for themselves or their families).  Raiding
the treasury was probably unnecessary.

- --Glenn

