rules for careful reading later, when I\'m not on-line.)

Pierre-Louis Constantin has developed what appears to be a very workable 
system.  I rolled up a few test characters using it, and found that it 
worked well.  One of its strong points is that it encourages more 
imagination on the part of the referee and player when generating a 
character.  Having to come up with Major and Minor Setbacks, as well as 
Special Duties, is a good spur to creativity.

When I was rolling up those characters, it made me be a bit less likely 
to go for "one more term" in the hopes of finally getting that last 
promotion.  If you stop getting promotions, the negative DM\'s start 
piling up and you realize you\'d better quit while you\'re ahead.  I like 
that. 

Pierre, in your write-up you mentioned that it wasn\'t complete.  If you 
ever get the chance, it\'d be great if you would write up the complete 
system and share it with us.

Thanks for posting it!


- -Joe
