Interestingly enough, in one of the Star Trek novel, the author suggests that
Romulans feel the same way about names. The commander asks Kirk which great
Enterprise the ship is named for. When he replies that it isn\'t for any
specific enterprise, just the spirit, the commander is not surprised that
the ship gets into so much trouble. Call a ship Intrepid, and it will
forget how to fear (especially if you crew it with Vulcans), and get into
trouble.

