    'index' => 'ae376',
    'body' => 'On 07/04/96 at 10:19 AM,  Joe Walsh <ransom@connect.iconnect.net>
said:

>On Thu, 4 Jul 1996, Andrew Whincup wrote:

>> I only really have experience of MT but in MHO I feel that 
>> the background is intrinsic to what traveller is....what makes
>> traveller special is the feel of the game and this comes from the way
>> the background and the rules work together,

I\'m going to disagree with you, Andrew! <g>  

It\'s not the background, exactly.  It\'s not the rules, or how the
background and rules work together either.  It\'s the FEEL of the game.
(If I could really explain this, I\'d bottle it.  <g>)

>In a way, you are right that the rules are, in many ways, part and
>parcel  of the Imperial setting.  For example, the oft-cited price
>fixing for  cargo and passage rates.  

Yeah, but how many of us have developed house rules for this, that,
and the other thing...like price fixing and passage rates.  I bet if
we add up all the house rules, you wouldn\'t recognize the *rules*, but
you would recognize the feel of the game.

>But, here\'s another look at the issue:

>The Traveller set I first purchased was the Deluxe Starter Edition
>(two  8-1/2 by 11" booklets, with Adventure 0, Introduction to
>Traveller, and  the Spinward Marches map. 

Mine was the original Black Box with 3 little black books that never
mentioned anything about the Imperium..period.  No adventures!  No
map!  Totally "roll your own", so we did.

>We hadn\'t used prepared adventures since the D&D days, so I didn\'t
>actually read Adventure 0 until about 10 years later (!).  I don\'t
>recall reading Intro to.., either.

Having never owned either, I haven\'t either.  <g> Actually, I think
"Intro to.." was published in JTAS or Challenge, I think, so I might
have read it.

>So, we set about  playing Traveller using only the core
>rules.  I made up planets as I went  along.  There was no "Imperium." 

Right! Traveller could be anything you wanted...still can.

>Then I bought Supplement 3, The Spinward Marches and that gave me
>data on  the planets on my map. 

When I bought Supplement 3 I\'d never seen a map.  It provided a
*wonderful* playground that I could do with what I wanted.  I\'d
developed several star systems by then and just integrated them into
the Spinward Marches.  Those were the days my friend!

>But there still wasn\'t an Imperium. 

Actually, I started seeing it referred to in JTAS, and Book 5 (High
Guard) actually *assumed* some sort of remote centralized government.
I think they were calling it the Imperium even then.

>Gradually, our campaign environment came to resemble the official
>Traveller universe.

I guess mine did too, but we never got too close to the official
history.  Remember how we all felt when WAR! splashed across the JTAS
cover?  <g> It was very exciting, but my games never got involved in
the 5th Frontier War...and we skipped the rebellion, the civil war,
and the V\'thing in their entirety.

>Now, did our play suffer from not using the Imperium?  No, it didn\'t.
 
Absolutely not!  

I *loved* the Traveller News, went there first in every issue of JTAS
and Challenge, but all that was happening in a different universe.  A
similar universe, with similar technologies and star systems, but
still a different one.

>The rules, the clarity, the  professionalism...these things made
>Traveller the superior product it was  for us.

You got that right!  I just turned and look up at my bookshelf saw
GURPS, Aftermath, Space Opera, SpaceMaster, Star Trek and
StarFrontiers all sitting there..along with CT, MT, TNE, TW2K, and
2300AD.  <G> (The rest of my stuff is in another room) They are all
grist for the mill!  

Only Traveller keeps rising to the top.

>I still hope the rules will be separate from the setting - even
>if  only separated into sections of the same book.  That way, people
>will at  least have the clear choice of making their own setting.

I do to.  I keep going back to TNE, looking at the rules, and dang it!
There are some really good ideas in there.  It\'s just so *hard* to
find them among all the setting stuff.  

Give me the rules!  I\'ll come up with the setting!  Ok, you can give
me the setting too..just make it easy to separate the two.  <g>


Eris
