The only novels I know of with a lion named Aslan are the Chronicles of 
Narnia series by C.S. Lewis (which, incidentally, were the first novels I 
read all the way through of my own accord, and which were a big reason I 
learned to enjoy reading as much as I do!  After them I read C.S. Lewis\' 
