    'topic' => 'Earth (lots of questions)',
    'body' => 'I\'m curious to learn more about how the Earth of 5700AD is presented in the
published material, which I never got a chance to see.  What are the major
cities, the population, the political setup and the tech-level?  Where is
the starport(s) located?  

I was struck by the fact (mentioned on the list recently) that the people of
5700AD are as far removed from us as we are from those of 1700BC, the bronze
age of ancient mesopotamia and Middle Kingdom Egypt.  Thus to the Solomani
on the eve of the Virus spaceflight is as old as iron is to us and London,
New York and Moscow are as remote as Nineveh and Ur. 

So what does the average citizen of Terra know of Earth\'s long long history?
Again, by analogy with the past, will the names of Washington, Lenin and
Napoleon be as obscure as those of Hammurabi and Thutmose?  I assume that
(probably partial) historical records will survive but they are likely to be
the province of specialist historians and linguists who will produce
closely-argued PhD\'s proving that spaceflight was invented during an obscure
100-year period of violence and fluid alliances called either "The World
War" or "Cold War".

Comments (and PhD titles :-)) please.

Jamie

