Hm. I\'d argue that Brass->Iron is more of a leap than Iron->Bonded Superdense,
but I\'m not sure how.
 
> So what does the average citizen of Terra know of Earth\'s long long history?

Probably lots. if there\'s one thing that human have gotten better at over
the centuries (millenia!) it\'s keeping records. We know as much as we
do about Ancient Mesopotamia because they kept such good records on clay
tablets and such. Modern people produce such vast amounts of information
about themselves that we\'ll probably go down as the greatest narcicists (sp?)
