This jogged a memory loose. I\'ve seen plans for something very similar
to this in a 1940s vintage _Popular Mechanics_ or _Popular Science_.
The gizmo used an electric motor to spin a tube around it\'s centerpoint.
Each end of the tube was curved into something like a Jai Alai racket
shape. A hopper fed BBs into the hub of the tube, centrifugal force
spun the BBs out through the tubes. There was some sort of interruptor
mechanism to ensure the BBs would release from one point.

The photo showed a happy home handyman playing with his electric indoor
