One of the things which the MT collapse supplement ("Hard Times" ?) 
pointed out was how many planets are dependent on off-world 
technology or off-world resources. Many TL 6-8 worlds are going to be 
borderline at best when it comes to sustaining their life support 
systems. Many non-agricultural worlds are going to have problems 
supporting themselves (dependent on food imports). Also, many 
low-population planets which lose contact with the local starfaring 
culture are going to be in serious trouble -- think of the problems 
they will have with a limited gene pool (interesting adventure 
scenarios: think of "Deliverance"). Milieu 0 explorers are likely to
find quite a few dead worlds, with ruined settlements.

