    'body' => 'Here\'s a comic book science explanation of cold fusion:

When you insert metal alloy rods of a special configuration into ordinary
water and then run an electric current through the mechanism, the metal alloy
rods serve as a catalyst (that is, they promote the reaction, but are
unchanged by it) which promotes fusion of hydrogen into helium.

The result is a production of energy as a current flow from the mechanism
