    'body' => 'Please tale me out from your list, and don\'t send me any more e-mail.  Thank
you.

>>OK so I have this ground vehicle with a Radar installed (range: distant).
>>How do I use this in the game?
>
>        I figure a futuristic radar setup would have both ground sensing
>and air-sweeping radar. For Ground radar, you will be able to detect (and
>possibly image) any moving object within line of sight (less than 100m in
>forest, greater than 2km in desert). Air-sweeping radar will detect out to
>the horizon (70km) in perfectly flat terrain (calm ocean), significantly
>less in rough terrain (1-2km), and virtually nil in a depression.
>Sophisticated radar systems will also be able to recognize pre-programmed
>objects (enemy tanks, aircraft).
>
>       Attack radar is usually a seperate system, though by 5700ad I figure
>scan-while-track will be common. I figure a sensors roll (range and terrain
>dependant) will be necessary to obtain a lock-on. Once locked on, all
>radar-assisted guns (with balistic computers) will fire one level easier,
>and guided ordinance (missiles, etc) will hit 80-90% of the time.
>
>        Radar detectors will also be activated both by the sweeping and
>attack radars. This will allow the pilot/driver to jinx, deploy ECM, or
>fire anti-radiation missiles (missiles that home in on the radar signal).
>The effectiveness of this is up to you. The strongest consideration should
>be the Tech level, I would say each tech level difference reduces
>effectiveness by half (for both radar, and countermeasures).
>
>                                                                Matt
>
>
>
