    'topic' => 'X-boat proposal',
    'body' => 'On the X-boat proposals:

Check the date _very carefully_ against the Civil War material.  I don\'t
think that the network could have been established until Arbatrella
was  in full control (at least as Regent, if not as Empress).  Include
a paragraph or so about how Arbatrella intended to reduce the chances
of another Civil War by tying the Imperium more closely together. 
(Background is always good.  Book 9: Fighting Ships was about 300%
more useful than  Fighting Ships of the Shattered Imperium because
it included a couple paragraphs of actual _text_ about each ship,
as opposed to just the stats.)

The section about "X-boats didn\'t become Vampire ships" should be 
deleted.  Sure, they couldn\'t refuel... but the computer might very
well be infected with Virus, which then goes dormant as the power
fails.  And I\'m sure X-boats had anti-intruder measures just in
case a pirate dcided to start preying on the communication lines.


Tony Z

