Dear Stephen,
 
The managers of Traveller seem  very enthusiastic about DGP being
involved in  the development of  Traveller once again,  including
the possibility of  DGP archiving all of its  material on CD-ROM.
They have remained enthusiastic throughout our negotiations.
 
Unfortunately (or quite fortunately, dependending on how you look
at it)  the managers of Traveller  have their hands full  and are
extremely  busy.  This  means  they  are  working  hard  to  make
Traveller  the best  that it  can  be  -- something  we will  all
benefit  from.  I\'m  thoroughly  impressed  with  what  I\'ve seen
(including what\'s going on behind-the-scenes).
 
As for  placing a % probability  on DGP\'s chances of  getting the
official  go-ahead, it\'s  more a  matter of  when rather than how
likely, and  that\'s anybody\'s guess.  Though I\'m sure Marc Miller
and his associates will get around to us just as soon as they are
able to.
 
Keep your fingers crossed.
 
Sincerely,
 
Roger Sanger
Digest Group Publications
