    'topic' => ' Sand casters and Book Three',
    'body' => 'Leonard Erickson wrote (about sandcasters):
> I think that sand covered the hex your ship was in when you fired it.
> And it kept moving with the vector your ship had when you fired it.
> Thus if you manuevered, you\'d leave the sand cloud behind, following
> your old course. Note that "manuevering" includes accelerating in the
> same direction..

Nice post, Leonard.  I\'ve been following this discussion to get my own brain thinking in 
the right direction about sandcasters, and as I remember, you are right.

I must also say that I like the improvement in T4 where the sand particles are 
magnetised so that the sand cloud can be moved with the ship by a magnetic beam (and, I 
assume, the highest desity of the cloud can be placed between the ship and incoming 
fire).

In my universe, I think I\'ll use both ideas.  One is for lower tech ships, and one is 
for higher tech ships.  Just like Heplar and thruster plates.

Kenneth.


